  "text": "Our aim is to provide a sufficient condition for the continuity of the minimum time function in this framework, i.e., sufficient conditions granting Small Time Local Attainability (STLA) in the sense of [CITATION_1] . The paper is structured as follows: in Section 2 we fix the notation and review some basic results about measure theory, optimal transport and set-valued analysis, in Section 3 we prove some basic properties of the admissible trajectories in the space of measures, in Section 4 we discuss some geometric properties of the target sets, and finally in Section 5 we state our main result concerning the continuity of the minimum time function.",
